    <section class="page-section">
      <h2 class="page-section__title">Security &amp; integrity</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How is evidence integrity maintained?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>Every piece of evidence is hashed using SHA-256 at the point of intake. All subsequent access, transformations, and exports are logged in immutable, append-only audit records. Processing is deterministic — the same inputs always produce the same outputs.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can original evidence be modified or deleted?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>No. Original evidence is stored as immutable. The system does not permit overwrites, edits, or deletions of source material. Derived outputs are always linked back to and verifiable against their originals.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is audit log data ever purged?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>Audit logs are append-only and are never deleted or overwritten. This is required for chain-of-custody integrity and evidentiary admissibility.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

      </div>
    </section>

